To make the background of an image transparant in gimp:(Mostly for logos)

Ensure the image is in png format

You now need to add an alpha layer
Layer>transparancy>Add alpha layer. (If it is grayed out, you may already have an alpha layer)

Select the background either by the fuzzy select tool U , or Select by colour shft o.

Deselect to stop the marching ants Select>none.

